CAVIN Johnson has joined Black Leopards. The former AmaZulu coach was introduced to the players on Sunday morning. The 61-year-old mentor replace Luc Eymael who resigned from the job on Friday. According to reports, Eymael was left frustrated by the club's reluctance to sign more players in the January transfer window.However, the Belgian mentor cited personal reasons for his decision to leave his post. Johnson will become the third coach to be in charge of Lidoda Duvha in a short period of six months. Leopards started the season under the tutelage of Lionel Soccoia who was fired after two months following a string of bad results. 